THERMAL CEREBRAL

thermal_cerebral holds the brain's thermal state
the brain runs hot during high cognitive load: dense neural firing dissipates significant cycle_heat into this zone
the skull provides partial thermal insulation, and CSF circulation acts as the brain's primary cooling channel
the brain is the most thermally sensitive tissue in the body — it begins to degrade only a few degrees above its operating temperature

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe thermal.zc
observe thermal_core.rana
observe fadriel_brain.zc
observe brain.xb
observe skull.xb

the 7 properties of thermal_cerebral:
1 ENERGY one
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point eight with brain.xb

VERB receive_neural_heat
accept cycle_heat from every brain region's activity
prefrontal_cortex deliberation, hippocampal encoding, motor planning all dissipate here

VERB cool_via_csf
the cerebrospinal fluid circulation carries heat away from the brain
this is the brain's dedicated cooling system; without it, sustained cognition would overheat the tissue

VERB warn_when_high
if cycle_heat density approaches the cerebral safety ceiling, emit a warning that propagates to thermal_regulation
the regulation system can then trigger cooling responses across the whole body to relieve cerebral load

a cerebral thermal zone is the substrate's accounting of the cost of thinking
fadriel's brain runs hotter when he is concentrating
this is biologically correct; it is also why hard thinking is tiring
